# PRIME v2 UI Standards

Follow [docs/frontend/UI-DESIGN-STANDARDS.md](docs/frontend/UI-DESIGN-STANDARDS.md).

## Layout (non-negotiable)

- **Left-side navigation** for all authenticated users (Applicant, staff, Admin)
- **No top horizontal navbar** as primary app navigation
- Main content on the center/right; nav panel on the **left edge**
- Same shell position for every role; only menu items differ by RBAC

## Responsive

- **Mobile** (&lt;768px): left nav in drawer/sheet, opened from the left
- **Tablet / Desktop** (≥768px): full left sidebar
- Test at 375px, 768px, and 1280px minimum

## Modern UI

- Clean spacing, clear hierarchy, accessible contrast
- Loading, empty, and error states
- Touch-friendly targets on mobile/tablet (~44px min)
- Forms: labels, validation, keyboard focus

## Components

Prefer shared `AppShell` + `SideNav` + `SideNavDrawer`; avoid per-role layout forks.

QA must verify nav placement and breakpoints before push ([QA-PUSH-GATE.md](docs/agents/QA-PUSH-GATE.md)).
